    Run Multiple Assessments on a Study

    Study_Assess.Rd

    Study_Assess() attempts to run multiple assessments using a shared set of data (lData) and an associated data mapping (lMapping). By default, the rawplus data and associated mapping from the clindata package is used, and all assessments defined in inst/assessments are evaluated. Individual assessments are run using gsm::RunAssessment()

    Study_Assess(
  lData = NULL,
  lMapping = NULL,
  lAssessments = NULL,
  lSubjFilters = NULL,
  lTags = list(Study = "myStudy"),
  bQuiet = FALSE
)

    Arguments

    lData

    a named list of domain level data frames. Names should match the values specified in lMapping and lAssessments, which are generally based on the expected inputs from X_Map_Raw.

    lMapping

    a named list identifying the columns needed in each data domain.

    lAssessments

    a named list of metadata defining how each assessment should be run. By default, MakeAssessmentList() imports YAML specifications from inst/assessments.

    lSubjFilters

    Optionally specify Subject-level filters that will be applied to all assessments. For example list(strRandFlagCol="Y") could be used to subset to Randomized Participants.

    lTags

    a named list of Tags to be passed to each assessment. Default is list(Study="myStudy") could be expanded to include other important metadata such as analysis population or study phase.

    bQuiet

    Default is TRUE, which means warning messages are suppressed. Set to FALSE to see warning messages.

    Value

    A list of assessments containing status information and results.
